trong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/fernando-villavicencio-ecuador-assassinated-presidential-candidate" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/10/keep-a-gun-under-your-pillow-life-with-an-undercover-officer-in-northern-ireland" target="_blank">Keep a gun under your pillow: life with an undercover officer in Northern Ireland</a></h2><div class="description"> Susan Phoenix learned valuable lessons during her husband's clandestine career during the Troubles. When answering the phone, do not give your name or number. Check if are you being followed and if suspicious, double back. Let the dogs out first at night – they will tell if strangers are nearby.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 17:36:24 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/10/keep-a-gun-under-your-pillow-life-with-an-undercover-officer-in-northern-ireland" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/10/donald-trump-on-fresh-prince-morrissey-on-brookie-the-most-awful-celebrity-tv-cameos-ever-committed" target="_blank">Donald Trump on Fresh Prince? Morrissey on Brookie? The most awful celebrity TV cameos ever committed</a></h2><div class="description"> Former Strictly Come Dancing professional AJ Pritchard revealed he is terrible at acting. He was responsible for the viral ‘How’s Trish?’ clip, co-starring his equally acting-challenged brother Curtis. We charted the most terrible television appearances made by famous people who cannot act.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 13:58:50 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/10/donald-trump-on-fresh-prince-morrissey-on-brookie-the-most-awful-celebrity-tv-cameos-ever-committed" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/10/michael-imperioli-i-still-give-morrissey-the-benefit-of-the-doubt" target="_blank">Michael Imperioli: ‘I still give Morrissey the benefit of the doubt'</a></h2><div class="description"> The actor, writer and musician answers your questions on Buddhism, The Sopranos and his musical heroes. The first time you saw My Bloody Valentine you had to leave afterwards because you were so blown away. Have you had a live music experience like that since? dennylayne.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 13:08:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/10/michael-imperioli-i-still-give-morrissey-the-benefit-of-the-doubt" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/11/last-year-i-began-an-affair-his-marriage-is-over-now-but-how-can-i-survive-his-separation" target="_blank">Last year I began an affair. His marriage is over now, but how can I survive his separation? | Leading questions</a></h2><div class="description"> You and your partner need to be able to tolerate some recrimination, writes columnist Eleanor Gordon-Smith. She says it could be hard to move on from an affair with a man you met in your teens. He was 20 years into a marriage that he'd been miserable in for half that time.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 15:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/11/last-year-i-began-an-affair-his-marriage-is-over-now-but-how-can-i-survive-his-separation" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/10/dining-across-the-divide-grainne-marlon" target="_blank">Dining across the divide: ‘He’s definitely more eat-the-rich and I’m a bit more nibble at them’</a></h2><div class="description"> Both are republicans and agree on Boris Johnson and banning private schools. But will they see eye-to-eye on inheritance? They are both republicans, agree on everything from Boris Johnson to Boris's ban on private schools? Here's how to find out if you're going to inherit your inheritance.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 11:30:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/10/dining-across-the-divide-grainne-marlon" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/beach-leave-my-body-alone-women-marseille-app-france" target="_blank">When I’m on the beach, leave me and my body alone, s’il vous plaît | Marie Le Conte</a></h2><div class="description"> Marseille’s anti-abuse app helps, but it shouldn’t be necessary. It took moving to Britain and occasionally returning home to have this epiphany about my corporeal state. It's just that when you're in France and you're a woman, some men like to remind you of the fact.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 14:24:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/beach-leave-my-body-alone-women-marseille-app-france" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/northern-ireland-data-breach-police-safety" target="_blank">We know the risks of policing Northern Ireland, but this data breach exposes us as never before | Andrew George</a></h2><div class="description"> Our surname and initials, as well as our place of work, were released into the public domain in a data breach that disclosed the details of 10,000 police officers and staff. The ongoing terrorist threat in Northern Ireland made the news hard to swallow. There are still some officers of different communities who do not divulge what they do for a living to protect themselves and those around them.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 07:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/northern-ireland-data-breach-police-safety" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/10/ben-jennings-on-the-tory-deputy-chair-and-small-boat-arrivals-cartoon" target="_blank">Ben Jennings on the Tory deputy chair and small boat arrivals – cartoon</a></h2><div class="description"> CNN.com will feature iReporter photos in a weekly Travel Snapshots gallery. Please submit your best shots for next week's gallery of iReporters. Visit CNN iReport.com/Travel next Wednesday for a new gallery of snapshots of the world's most beautiful beaches.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 19:00:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/10/ben-jennings-on-the-tory-deputy-chair-and-small-boat-arrivals-cartoon" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/the-secret-to-maintaining-your-youthful-passion-i-learned-it-this-week" target="_blank">The secret to maintaining your youthful passion? I learned it this week | Adrian Chiles</a></h2><div class="description"> Three decades a rock star is some innings but Sharleen Spiteri has found a way to stay motivated. The lead singer of Texas seems to have changed hardly at all in the three decades that have passed. Adrian Chiles was in his early 20s, stuck at home with a broken leg.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 10:00:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/the-secret-to-maintaining-your-youthful-passion-i-learned-it-this-week" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/barbie-shameless-product-placement-film-adverts-global-cinema" target="_blank">Let's not forget the real star of Barbie: shameless product placement | Amelia Tait</a></h2><div class="description"> Greta Gerwig’s Barbie is a 114-minute advert for the toy company Mattel. The film is like a Russian doll of adverts, each one nestled within the next, all contained within a giant, plastic doll. As the global product placement market grows, is this the future of blockbuster cinema?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 15:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/barbie-shameless-product-placement-film-adverts-global-cinema" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/private-jets-are-awful-for-the-climate-its-time-to-tax-the-rich-who-fly-in-them" target="_blank">Private jets are awful for the climate. It’s time to tax the rich who fly in them | Edward J Markey</a></h2><div class="description"> Private flights pollute up to 14 times more than commercial ones – yet are taxed less. Let’s change that. Tax-dodging ultra-wealthy need to stop fueling the problem and start supporting first-class solutions. Edward J Markey is a US senator from Massachusetts.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 10:02:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/private-jets-are-awful-for-the-climate-its-time-to-tax-the-rich-who-fly-in-them" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/jamie-reid-sex-pistols-artwork-punk" target="_blank">Jamie Reid’s Sex Pistols artwork was a glorious assault on authority | Jonathan Jones</a></h2><div class="description"> Artist Jamie Reid had a premonition of punk years before it hit. His 1972 painting Monster on a Nice Roof foretells the monster that was punk. The late artist gave punk its sharp edges and revolutionary force – and by attacking Putin, carried it into the present.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 11:27:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/jamie-reid-sex-pistols-artwork-punk" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/tory-voters-net-zero-environmental-action" target="_blank">The truth is Tory voters are onboard for net zero. What’s really worrying them is how we get there | Sam Hall</a></h2><div class="description"> The case for environmental action is clear, but there are fears about personal freedom and who will bear the financial burden. Conservatives want to protect our planet, but that doesn’t mean they’ll agree on every policy campaigners propose. The public wants the debate to focus on how, not if, we reach carbon neutrality.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 10:00:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/tory-voters-net-zero-environmental-action" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/the-guardian-view-on-northern-irelands-data-leak-putting-lives-at-risk" target="_blank">The Guardian view on Northern Ireland’s data leak: putting lives at risk | Editorial</a></h2><div class="description"> A new documentary film recounts a grim story from the Northern Ireland Troubles. Thomas Niedermayer was a German businessman living in Belfast. He was kidnapped from his home by the IRA, possibly to be traded for imprisoned bombers. His body was found in a shallow grave in 1980. Ten years on, his widow, Ingeborg, took her own life. A year after that, his younger daughter Renate, Renate and Gabriella also killed themselves.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 17:28:02 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/10/the-guardian-view-on-northern-irelands-data-leak-putting-lives-at-risk" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/10/its-time-to-professionalise-our-underemployed-mps" target="_blank">It’s time to professionalise our underemployed MPs | Letters</a></h2><div class="description"> Too many MPs are treating their job as a springboard to a lucrative sideline. This practice debases the high office they hold and, by extension, parliament itself. It seems we can no longer count on altruism and vocational motivation in our elected representatives. It’s time we professionalise the role of MP, to make the post-holder accountable to taxpayers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 16:34:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/10/its-time-to-professionalise-our-underemployed-mps" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/10/scout-jamboree-does-not-deserve-this-ill-judged-attack" target="_blank">Scout jamboree does not deserve this ill-judged attack | Letter</a></h2><div class="description"> Janet Kay was taken aback by the letter about the UK contingent to the World Scout Jamboree in South Korea. The writer implied that these scouts had been whisked to air-conditioned hotels at the slightest sign of discomfort. The children learn how to work in teams and to be self-reliant, she writes.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 16:34:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/10/scout-jamboree-does-not-deserve-this-ill-judged-attack" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2023/aug/10/spain-v-netherlands-womens-world-cup-2023-quarter-final-live" target="_blank">Spain v Netherlands: Women’s World Cup 2023 quarter-final – live</a></h2><div class="description"> Back-to-back Ballon d’Or winner Alexia Putellas is NOT in the Spain squad. She hasn’t been in top form after an ACL injury last year. The lineup is basically anyone who plays for Barcelona or Real Madrid -- each club has nine players.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 00:32:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2023/aug/10/spain-v-netherlands-womens-world-cup-2023-quarter-final-live" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/lauren-james-gets-two-game-ban-clearing-her-for-final-if-england-get-there" target="_blank">Lauren James gets two-game ban, clearing her for final if England get there</a></h2><div class="description"> England forward Lauren James was sent off for stamp on Nigeria's Michelle Alozie. Forward was given a yellow card for the incident but it was upgraded to a red after a VAR intervention. James has been given a two-game suspension for her stamp on the Nigeria player. England face Colombia in World Cup quarter-finals in Brazil.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 13:53:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/lauren-james-gets-two-game-ban-clearing-her-for-final-if-england-get-there" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2023/aug/10/how-to-win-a-penalty-shootout-womens-world-cup-england" target="_blank">How to win a penalty shootout: prepare, be smart – and win the toss</a></h2><div class="description"> England beat Nigeria on penalties at the Women’s World Cup on penalties. Millie Bright won the coin toss and chose to kick first in the shootout. Professor Ignacio Palacios-Huerta says the main advantage is going first. He says it is not a 50-50, rather a 60-40 advantage towards whoever goes first.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 15:36:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2023/aug/10/how-to-win-a-penalty-shootout-womens-world-cup-england" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2023/aug/11/premier-league-10-things-to-look-out-for-on-the-opening-weekend" target="_blank">Premier League: 10 things to look out for on the opening weekend</a></h2><div class="description"> Vincent Kompany's old club provide a litmus test for his current one for the second time in six months. Burnley were storming towards the Championship title and unbeaten in 18 matches when pitted away at Manchester City in the FA Cup quarter-finals in March. City officials viewed the tie as a gauge of Burnley’s Premier League credentials.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 23:01:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2023/aug/11/premier-league-10-things-to-look-out-for-on-the-opening-weekend" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/tottenham-accept-harry-kane-offer-bayern-munich" target="_blank">Harry Kane’s big decision imminent after Spurs accept Bayern Munich’s offer</a></h2><div class="description"> Harry Kane is weighing up whether to join Bayern Munich and end his 19-year stay at Tottenham. The two clubs have agreed a deal that could be worth almost £100m. Kane is leaning towards a move to Germany, with a medical pencilled in for Friday after talks gathered pace.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 23:13:02 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/tottenham-accept-harry-kane-offer-bayern-munich" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/10/tom-pidcock-accused-of-causing-crash-world-championship-bronze-cross-country-short-track-cycling" target="_blank">‘He rode into me’: Tom Pidcock accused of causing crash on way to world bronze</a></h2><div class="description"> Olympic cross-country champion Tom Pidcock accused of unsportsmanlike riding. Luca Schwarzbauer was in third before last-corner incident in Glentress Forest near Peebles. Schwarzbauau was in bronze medal position as the lead group entered the final corner.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 19:23:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/10/tom-pidcock-accused-of-causing-crash-world-championship-bronze-cross-country-short-track-cycling" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/10/caution-will-not-win-this-world-cup-england-need-to-find-attacking-fluency" target="_blank">Caution will not win this World Cup: England need to find attacking fluency | Robert Kitson</a></h2><div class="description"> Pressure is growing on Steve Borthwick to get more out of the crowd-pleasing talents that undoubtedly exist within his squad. The World Cup is unlikely to be won by sides simply content to sit back and wait for opponents to make mistakes. On firm, dry pitches a cutting edge from first phase as well as turnover ball is going to be essential.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 18:20:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/10/caution-will-not-win-this-world-cup-england-need-to-find-attacking-fluency" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/saudi-pro-league-new-season-big-stars-fervour" target="_blank">Saudi Pro League has the big stars – now it has to hope the fervour follows</a></h2><div class="description"> Saudi Pro League season kicks off on Friday night in Saudi Arabia. Lavish spending has generated hype and controversy, but how will this project play out once the season starts? A video billboard in Jeddah welcomes those heading into the city along the airport road with a glowing portrait of the stars. Elsewhere, however, it is difficult to detect much Pro League fever as Saudi Arabia prepares for the big kick-off.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 21:12:11 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/saudi-pro-league-new-season-big-stars-fervour" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/10/ally-ewing-takes-first-round-lead-at-womens-open-as-big-names-struggle" target="_blank">Ally Ewing takes first round lead at Women’s Open as big names struggle</a></h2><div class="description"> American Ewing, the world No 39, one clear after round of 68 at Walton Heath. Ashleigh Buhai, Céline Boutier and Georgia Hall all two over. Amy Yang and Jeongeun Lee6 shot rounds of 69 along with Jaravee Boonchant, Perrine Delacour and Emily Kristine Pedersen.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 20:26:26 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/10/ally-ewing-takes-first-round-lead-at-womens-open-as-big-names-struggle" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/10/shabnim-ismail-hat-trick-last-three-balls-seals-hundred-victory-welsh-fire-cricket" target="_blank">Shabnim Ismail’s hat-trick in last three balls seals unlikely Hundred victory</a></h2><div class="description"> Birmingham Phoenix had needed four runs to win off last three balls. Welsh Fire bowler Shabnim Ismail took hat-trick in dramatic Hundred victory. Birmingham Phoenix beaten by three runs at Edgbaston by Welsh Fire. Ismail's ice-cool display prevented the home side scoring any of the four runs they needed.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 20:44:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/10/shabnim-ismail-hat-trick-last-three-balls-seals-hundred-victory-welsh-fire-cricket" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/10/i-should-be-in-lapland-robert-helenius-anthony-joshua" target="_blank">‘I should be in Lapland’: Helenius gave up family holiday to fight Joshua</a></h2><div class="description"> The Nordic Nightmare is determined to make the most of his late opportunity just seven days after his last contest. He had just fought the 36th bout of his career when he beat his Finnish compatriot Mika Mielonen on a third-round stoppage. The fight was held in a 15th-century castle in Savonlinna, Finland.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 19:00:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/10/i-should-be-in-lapland-robert-helenius-anthony-joshua" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/10/return-of-el-nino-raises-risk-of-hunger-drought-and-malaria-scientists-warn" target="_blank">Return of El Niño raises risk of hunger, drought and malaria, scientists warn</a></h2><div class="description"> Hot natural weather pattern will exacerbate heat-related dangers brought about by climate crisis. Scientists fear it will raise the risk in some countries of hunger, drought and malaria. The return of El Niño against the backdrop of the climate crisis will hurt people’s health in many parts of the world.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 17:54:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/10/return-of-el-nino-raises-risk-of-hunger-drought-and-malaria-scientists-warn" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/10/water-wars-meet-guardians-one-of-europes-vital-wetlands-donana-national-park-spain" target="_blank">Water wars: meet the guardians of one of Europe’s most vital wetlands</a></h2><div class="description"> Doñana national park in Andalucía, Spain, is being threatened by drought, over-consumption and rightwing MPs. People’s party (PP) and far-right Vox party pushing to legalise irrigation in the park. Despite warnings from Unesco and the European Commission, the People's party and Vox party are pushing for legalising irrigation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 11:00:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/10/water-wars-meet-guardians-one-of-europes-vital-wetlands-donana-national-park-spain" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/african-penguins-could-be-extinct-by-2035-campaigners-say" target="_blank">African penguins could be extinct by 2035, campaigners say</a></h2><div class="description"> Population has declined dramatically due to overfishing and environmental changes in the Indian Ocean. In the early 20th century, there were probably several million breeding pairs. Today, fewer than 11,000 breeding pairs remain and population continues to fall sharply. Campaigners say penguins are on track for extinction by 2035 if measures are not taken.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 12:34:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/african-penguins-could-be-extinct-by-2035-campaigners-say" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/lula-brazil-amazon-rainforests-money" target="_blank">‘Nature needs money’: Lula tells rich countries to pay up and protect world’s rainforests</a></h2><div class="description"> Brazilian president says developed nations that over centuries have pumped emissions into the atmosphere must ‘pay their bit’ Major rainforest nations demand hundreds of billions of dollars of climate financing and a greater role in how those resources are spent. Lula: “It’s not Brazil that needs money. It's not Colombia or Venezuela,” Lula says.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:53:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/lula-brazil-amazon-rainforests-money" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/10/politicians-too-scared-to-take-on-tech-firms-says-former-senior-met-officer" target="_blank">Politicians too scared to take on tech firms, says former senior Met officer</a></h2><div class="description"> Former chief superintendent Dal Babu calls for financial penalties after social media posts attract hundreds of teenagers to London’s Oxford Street. Police issued 34 dispersal orders and arrested nine individuals on Wednesday after people gathered outside JD Sports in an apparent response to posts on Snapchat and TikTok urging users to take part in an ‘Oxford Circus JD robbery” at 3pm.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 18:40:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/10/politicians-too-scared-to-take-on-tech-firms-says-former-senior-met-officer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/10/nicola-sturgeon-has-faith-police-were-justified-in-searching-her-home" target="_blank">Nicola Sturgeon ‘has faith’ police were justified in searching her home</a></h2><div class="description"> Former Scottish first minister tells Edinburgh fringe show she has done nothing wrong but still trusts ‘the process’ She and her husband were arrested as part of the investigation into SNP’s finances. Nicola Sturgeon categorically rule out any reconciliation with her predecessor, Alex Salmond.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 17:08:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/10/nicola-sturgeon-has-faith-police-were-justified-in-searching-her-home" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/10/luke-brooks-mouldy-damp-house-did-not-cause-mans-death-coroner-rules" target="_blank">Mouldy, damp house did not cause man’s death, coroner rules</a></h2><div class="description"> Luke Brooks, 27, from Oldham, died at his home last October from an acute respiratory illness. Postmortem examination found aspergillus, a type of mould, on his lung. Coroner rules that he did not die because of conditions in the property.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 16:28:09 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/10/luke-brooks-mouldy-damp-house-did-not-cause-mans-death-coroner-rules" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/10/reform-planning-laws-protect-historic-pub-buildings-crooked-house" target="_blank">Change planning laws to protect historic pub buildings, campaigners say</a></h2><div class="description"> Call for government to act amid anger over demolition of Crooked House pub in Staffordshire. Greg Mulholland, director of Campaign for Pubs, said anger over fire and demolition of pub must act as 'catalyst for change' in approach to protecting historic pubs.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 18:00:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/10/reform-planning-laws-protect-historic-pub-buildings-crooked-house" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/10/dissident-republicans-claim-to-have-data-from-psni-breach-says-chief-constable" target="_blank">Dissident republicans claim to have data from PSNI breach, says chief constable</a></h2><div class="description"> Simon Byrne says he is ‘deeply sorry’ and that force is advising officers and staff about potential risks. Police Service of Northern Ireland’s ‘industrial-scale’ data breach, chief constable says. He said he was “deeply sorry’ about the mishandling of personal information.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 16:51:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/10/dissident-republicans-claim-to-have-data-from-psni-breach-says-chief-constable" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/10/natwest-and-virgin-money-cut-rates-as-mortgage-price-war-spreads" target="_blank">NatWest and Virgin Money cut rates as mortgage ‘price war’ spreads</a></h2><div class="description"> Big lenders become latest to reduce borrowing costs, joining four other UK home loan providers this week. Halifax reducing rates by up to 0.71 percentage points from Friday, and HSBC, Nationwide and TSB making similar moves. Move comes after it emerged on Wednesday that four of Britain’s largest lenders were cutting the cost of their new fixed-rate deals.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 17:28:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/10/natwest-and-virgin-money-cut-rates-as-mortgage-price-war-spreads" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/uk-minister-defends-plan-to-demand-access-to-encrypted-messages" target="_blank">UK minister defends plan to demand access to encrypted messages</a></h2><div class="description"> Technology secretary says move proposed in online safety bill is necessary to combat child abuse. Michelle Donelan said move strongly opposed by secure messaging firms and privacy campaigners. She said the move was necessary to fight child abuse and was needed to protect the public. The move would force messaging apps to access private messages if requested by communications watchdog.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 14:38:07 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/uk-minister-defends-plan-to-demand-access-to-encrypted-messages" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2023/aug/10/almost-nine-in-10-students-in-england-feel-free-to-express-their-views-survey" target="_blank">Almost nine in 10 students in England feel free to express their views – survey</a></h2><div class="description"> 86% of final-year students in England feel free to express their opinions and beliefs. Only 3% said they were ‘not free at all’ to express views. Government-backed survey contrasts with claims of widespread ‘cancel culture’ on campuses.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 17:22:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2023/aug/10/almost-nine-in-10-students-in-england-feel-free-to-express-their-views-survey" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/10/tax-rises-and-subsidy-cuts-behind-drop-in-uk-household-incomes-says-oecd" target="_blank">Tax rises and subsidy cuts behind drop in UK household incomes, says OECD</a></h2><div class="description"> UK in bottom half of income table across 38 rich nations as US and Italy see growth but Canada, France and Germany decline. OECD said UK was bottom half in income table after steeper rise in tax payments than counterparts in US, France, Germany and Canada. OECD review of its 38 member states found UK was in the bottom half the income table.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 18:09:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/10/tax-rises-and-subsidy-cuts-behind-drop-in-uk-household-incomes-says-oecd" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/10/rnli-lifeboats-called-to-incident-in-channel" target="_blank">RNLI lifeboats rescue 17 people floating in Channel</a></h2><div class="description"> Four lifeboats from across Kent were called by HM Coastguard to respond after people were seen floating in the water. Charity says all those in difficulty taken to safety, as number arriving in the UK by this route may have reached 100,000. Total number of people arriving in UK by the route may now be at least 100,00.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 14:33:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/10/rnli-lifeboats-called-to-incident-in-channel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/indian-opposition-walks-out-as-narendra-modi-refuses-to-discuss-manipur-conflict" target="_blank">Indian opposition walks out as Narendra Modi refuses to discuss Manipur conflict</a></h2><div class="description"> Opposition parties walk out of Indian parliament in protest at PM's refusal to address ethnic violence in state of Manipur. PM attacks opposition parties during no-confidence motion called to force him to address violence in far-east. Situation described as being close to civil war in Manipur, India.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 17:24:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/indian-opposition-walks-out-as-narendra-modi-refuses-to-discuss-manipur-conflict" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/hawaii-fire-kills-people-lahaina-town-maui" target="_blank">Death toll from Hawaii wildfires increases to 53 as search for survivors continues</a></h2><div class="description"> Officials warned death toll could rise after wildfires left dozens injured and homes and businesses destroyed. The catastrophic fires are expected to become the state’s deadliest natural disaster since 1961 – when a tsunami killed 61 people. The governor said the death toll from the fires would likely exceed that figure.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 00:34:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/hawaii-fire-kills-people-lahaina-town-maui" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/10/russia-lunar-landing-mission-luna-25-moon" target="_blank">Moon rocket blasts off, carrying Russia’s hope of first successful lunar landing since 1976</a></h2><div class="description"> The unmanned Luna-25 mission launched in the early hours of Friday on a journey to the moon that is expected to take about five days. The mission will try to land near the south pole of the moon, seeking signs of water or its components. A landing date has not been announced.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 15:21:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/10/russia-lunar-landing-mission-luna-25-moon" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/west-african-leaders-activate-standby-force-to-put-pressure-on-junta-in-niger" target="_blank">West African leaders activate standby force to put pressure on junta in Niger</a></h2><div class="description"> Ecowas says force is a last resort and would prefer diplomatic means of reinstating President Bazoum after army coup. President Bola Tinubu of Nigeria warned that “no option is taken off the tables including the use of force as the last resort”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 18:07:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/west-african-leaders-activate-standby-force-to-put-pressure-on-junta-in-niger" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div 