></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/10/linda-yaccarino-says-twitter-will-reinstate-client-council-for-ad-execs" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/lil-tay-rapper-reported-death" target="_blank">‘I’m alive’: teen rapper Lil Tay releases statement after mysterious death report</a></h2><div class="description"> A statement on her official Instagram had claimed the 15-year-old girl had died but she has now claimed it was 'compromised' TMZ has now reported that she is still alive. An unsigned statement said the star’s death at 15 was “sudden and tragic” and “entirely unexpected” It also said that her older brother Jason Tian, who at one point had been in control of her account before it went dormant in 2018, had also died.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 18:05:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/lil-tay-rapper-reported-death" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/purdue-pharma-oxycontin-supreme-court-sacklers-bankruptcy-deal" target="_blank">US supreme court halts Purdue Pharma deal that shields Sacklers from lawsuits</a></h2><div class="description"> Court agrees to hear challenge from Biden administration to legality of OxyContin maker’s bankruptcy settlement. The settlement would shield its owners from lawsuits over their role in the country's opioid epidemic. The court also paused bankruptcy proceedings concerning Purdue and its affiliates and said in a brief order that it would hold oral arguments in December.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 20:53:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/purdue-pharma-oxycontin-supreme-court-sacklers-bankruptcy-deal" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/co-founder-of-russian-tech-giant-yandex-condemns-barbaric-war" target="_blank">Co-founder of Russian tech giant Yandex condemns ‘barbaric’ war</a></h2><div class="description"> Arkady Volozh, who lives in Israel, offers some of strongest criticism yet by a prominent Russian business figure. Yandex co-founder of Russia’s biggest internet firm, Arkady, said: “Russia's invasion of Ukraine is barbaric, and I am categorically against it”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 12:29:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/co-founder-of-russian-tech-giant-yandex-condemns-barbaric-war" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/cyprus-authorities-appeal-decision-that-allowed-david-hunter-to-walk-free" target="_blank">Cyprus authorities appeal against ruling that allowed David Hunter to walk free</a></h2><div class="description"> British pensioner found not guilty of premeditated murder of cancer-stricken wife. David Hunter faces further legal proceedings and possibility of jail. Cyprus’s highest legal authority appealed against decision of a district court that allowed him to walk free. Attorney general's office announced on Thursday it would appeal against sentence and acquittal of David Hunter.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 17:42:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/cyprus-authorities-appeal-decision-that-allowed-david-hunter-to-walk-free" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/10/bakla-review-this-teasing-tomfoolery-is-devilishly-smart" target="_blank">Baklâ review – this teasing tomfoolery is devilishly smart</a></h2><div class="description"> Max Percy’s physical theatre show mixes ideas on sex, power dynamics and homophobia into an audacious reflection on generational trauma. Baklâ is named after the Tagalog term for a third gender, a word that doubles as homophobic insult. The audience is treated variously as co-conspirators, voyeurs, clients and finally something close to oppressors.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 19:00:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/10/bakla-review-this-teasing-tomfoolery-is-devilishly-smart" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/10/last-voyage-demeter-movie-review-dracula-horror" target="_blank">The Last Voyage of the Demeter review – Dracula horror is lost at sea</a></h2><div class="description"> A chapter from Bram Stoker’s Dracula, set upon a ship, is expanded to a gory 2-hour film, an idea that works better in theory than in practice. Universal continues to find creative ways to rework its iconic monster movies in the shadow of the Dark Universe.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 18:53:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/10/last-voyage-demeter-movie-review-dracula-horror" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/noel-gallagher-admits-struggling-to-remember-lyrics-onstage" target="_blank">Noel Gallagher admits struggling to remember lyrics onstage</a></h2><div class="description"> Former Oasis member, now 56, suggests he may need to use teleprompter in future. Noel Gallagher has admitted he struggles to remember the words to some of the hits he created with his younger brother Liam in their band Oasis. The musician, 56, has suggested he may have to use a telepromripteater in the future.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 14:31:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/noel-gallagher-admits-struggling-to-remember-lyrics-onstage" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><di