anddesign/2023/aug/10/brice-marden-dies-aged-84" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/10/august-wilson-playwright-biography-film" target="_blank">‘One of the great American stories’: the incredible life of playwright August Wilson</a></h2><div class="description"> The legendary playwright’s humble beginnings and Pulitzer-winning career are explored in the first authoritative biography of him. August Wilson is one of the great playwrights of the 20th century and unofficial laureate of African American history and culture. The playwright's humble beginnings were explored in his first authoritative biography.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 15:04:02 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/10/august-wilson-playwright-biography-film" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">From Pig Beach to Dunn’s River Falls: 10 must-visit Caribbean destinations – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is home to the world’s best beaches, pretty towns, waterfalls and national parks. There are stunning marine life, the best beaches and pretty towns in the world's most beautiful places. Here's the Caribbean in all its glory, including some pretty towns and waterfalls.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:35:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">From snorkelling to surfing: nine must-try Caribbean beach and water activities</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean offers a huge variety of tempting activities from snorkelling to scuba diving. Windsurfing and waterskiing is a must-try activity for everyone. The Exu Exu is one of the Caribbean’s most beautiful, vividly coloured coral reefs.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:38:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Nightlife, loveseats and beautiful beaches: why the Caribbean makes for the perfect romantic holiday</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is an unbeatable destination for a romantic getaway with your loved one. From Jamaica to the hidden gem that is Curaçao, there’s something to suit every couple, whether on honeymoon, celebrating an anniversary, or just escaping everyday life for a taste of luxury.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:37:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Waterfalls, history and the world’s first underwater sculpture park: seven exciting things to do in the Caribbean</a></h2><div class="description"> The islands of the Caribbean are like nowhere else on Earth. From cocktails to coral reefs, they offer something for all tastes and tempos. Enjoy a classic mojito or piña colada on the white sand beaches of Barbados or Jamaica. Explore the area’s rich history and natural beauty.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:36:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/10/how-we-met-you-have-interesting-conversations-when-youre-half-naked-and-cold" target="_blank">How we met: ‘You have interesting conversations when you’re half-naked and cold!’</a></h2><div class="description"> Simonetta and Juliet, both 58, met during the pandemic at an outdoor swimming club. They now live in different parts of the world, but remain close friends. Simonetta enjoyed the occasional outdoor swim before she realised how beneficial it could be for her mental health. She joined the Serpentine Swimming Club in Hyde Park, close to where she lives.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 10:00:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/10/how-we-met-you-have-interesting-conversations-when-youre-half-naked-and-cold" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/10/versaces-new-owner-wants-to-be-a-big-beast-but-its-no-match-for-europes-behemoths" target="_blank">Versace’s new owner wants to be a big beast. But it’s no match for Europe’s behemoths</a></h2><div class="description"> Tapestry’s purchase of three big fashion names gives it heft. But LVMH and Kering have the front row to themselves. Coach, Michael Kors and Kate Spade New York have been the cornerstone of a particular type of New York fashion.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 18:21:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/10/versaces-new-owner-wants-to-be-a-big-beast-but-its-no-match-for-europes-behemoths" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/10/the-guardian-thursday-quiz-general-knowledge-topical-news-trivia-120" target="_blank">Crooked pubs, listed churches and scouting chaos – take the Thursday quiz</a></h2><div class="description"> You face 15 questions on the latest quirky news, general knowledge, and any number of obscure things that have caught the quiz master’s eye this week. Plus some jokes thrown in. How will you fare? Do let us know how you get on in the comments below.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 10:00:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/10/the-guardian-thursday-quiz-general-knowledge-topical-news-trivia-120" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/2023/aug/10/how-learning-to-swim-at-60-set-me-free" target="_blank">‘Move forward. Flap around a little!’ How learning to swim at 60 set me free</a></h2><div class="description"> Years of chronic neck and back spasms had stolen all the variety and fun I used to find in working out, especially that amped-up endorphin high. By his early 50s, I had spent thousands of dollars trying to mitigate this pain with alternative treatments. I was told swimming would make me fit and strong-minded, but first I had to navigate the slow lane.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/2023/aug/10/how-learning-to-swim-at-60-set-me-free" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/10/dream-holiday-at-home-how-i-holidayed-in-venice-without-leaving-york" target="_blank">‘Soaked and shivering, I order a spritz’: how I holidayed in Venice – without leaving York</a></h2><div class="description"> Unable to get to Italy, I spent a day recreating a Venetian mini-break in my home town. Who needs the Grand Canal when you’ve got the Ouse? Thankfully I live in York, which is also very old and full of locals complaining about tourists.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/10/dream-holiday-at-home-how-i-holidayed-in-venice-without-leaving-york" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/10/literary-dorset-pj-harvey-thomas-hardy-william-barnes" target="_blank">Of Thomas Hardy and PJ Harvey: on the trail of Dorset’s inspirational powers</a></h2><div class="description"> The county’s people, landscapes and villages have provided material for generations of writers. Thomas Hardy stamped his personality over his idea of Wessex, reviving an ancient kingdom and giving towns and villages new names. Every town seems to have been a film set for a Hardy adaptation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 06:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/10/literary-dorset-pj-harvey-thomas-hardy-william-barnes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/10/niger-coup-why-do-so-many-want-france-out-and-russia-in-video-explainer" target="_blank">Niger coup: why do so many want France out and Russia in? – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> On 26 July, a group of soldiers removed Niger's democratically elected president from power citing security concerns and economic mismanagement. Crowds waved Russian flags and chanted slogans against France, the country's former coloniser. Anti-French sentiment has rapidly become a key element of how the coup is being framed.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 13:37:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/10/niger-coup-why-do-so-many-want-france-out-and-russia-in-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/video/2023/aug/09/extreme-weather-glacial-flooding-wildfires-and-hailstorms-cause-havoc-across-the-world-video" target="_blank">Extreme weather: glacial flooding, wildfires and hailstorms cause havoc across the world  – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Countries across the globe are facing a range of extreme weather events. Severe flooding has affected parts of Europe including Sweden and Slovenia. Human-caused climate change is supercharging extreme weather across the world, driving more frequent and more deadly disasters, from heatwaves to floods to wildfires.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 14:36:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/video/2023/aug/09/extreme-weather-glacial-flooding-wildfires-and-hailstorms-cause-havoc-across-the-world-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Why Barcelona’s beaches are disappearing – video</a></h2><div class="description"> In 2010, Barcelona’s nine city beaches were topped up with 700,000 cubic metres of sand. Since then, 70% of that sand has disappeared. In the past 20 years the rate of erosion along Spain's east coast has been accelerating. It is partly to do with storms and rising sea levels but there are other factors at play.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 13 Jul 2023 08:46:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">I was a terrorist. Now I run a kindergarten – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendi Suhartono was part of a plot to detonate four book bombs and blow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved millions of lives and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">What is supercharging the global heat? – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> The planet is being hit with a double whammy of global heating in 2023: on top of the rise in global temperature caused by greenhouse gas emissions is an emerging El Niño. This sporadic event is the biggest natural influence on year-to-year weather and adds a further spurt of warmth to an already overheating world.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:48:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">How I survived a 'sex-ed shitstorm' – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Cartoonist Fiona Katauskas's book, The Amazing True Story of How Babies are Made, had been on Kmart and Big W shelves for three years. What started as a debate over the offending picture on Facebook would explode over several days into multiple headlines. Here is her take on what happened.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Playing Out is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children’s doorsteps. Some experts say a growing mental and physical health crisis could be a result. Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian's Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet Playing Out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2023/aug/10/wilko-employees-how-will-you-be-affected-by-the-retailer-entering-administration" target="_blank">Wilko employees: how will you be affected by the retailer entering administration?</a></h2><div class="description"> More than 12,000 jobs at risk after struggling to agree a rescue deal. The family-owned household and garden products retailer is expected to close dozens of outlets. We want to hear from workers at Wilko following the news that dozens of stores are expected to shut.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 15:04:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br